quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  60,7,"ňĻIn time,ňļ God may bring about goodwill between you and those of them you ňĻnowňļ hold as enemies. For God is Most Capable. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,God does not forbid you from dealing kindly and fairly with those who have neither fought nor driven you out of your homes. Surely God loves those who are fair
  60,9,"God only forbids you from befriending those who have fought you for ňĻyourňļ faith, driven you out of your homes, or supported ňĻothersňļ in doing so. And whoever takes them as friends, then it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentions‚ÄĒtheir faith¬†is best known to God‚ÄĒand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ňĻwomenňļ are not lawful ňĻwivesňļ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ňĻhusbandsňļ for them. ňĻButňļ repay the disbelievers whatever ňĻdowriesňļ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ňĻwomenňļ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ňĻButňļ demand ňĻrepayment ofňļ whatever ňĻdowriesňļ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of God‚ÄĒHe judges between you. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives desert you to the disbelievers, and later you take spoils from them, then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of whatever ňĻdowryňļ they had paid. And be mindful of God, in Whom you believe"
  60,12,"O Prophet! When the believing women come to you, pledging to you that they will neither associate anything with God ňĻin worshipňļ, nor steal, nor fornicate, nor kill their children, nor falsely attribute ňĻillegitimateňļ children to their husbands,¬†nor disobey you in what is right, then accept their pledge, and ask God to forgive them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,13,"O believers! Do not ally yourselves with a people God is displeased with. They already have no hope for the Hereafter, just like the disbelievers lying in ňĻtheirňļ graves"